{
  "article_id": "CambridgeChronicle1853",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "A correspondent of the San Francisco Transcript says that several leagues off "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in the Pacific, there is "
      },
      {
        "text": "a cluster of small Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which were at one time inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a numerous population of Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "These Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "carried on a considerable trade with the tribes on the main land, and with "
      },
      {
        "text": "the missions of Alta California",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Finally, from some cause or other, nearly all "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", gradually settled down among the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Inez",
        "entity_key": "mi_sy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angelos",
        "entity_key": "mi_sfern",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sg",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "entity_key": "mi_sd",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "One of the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "however, called "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", continued to be inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who could not be induced by any persuasions, to leave "
      },
      {
        "text": "their seagirt home",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "About the year 1825 ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was visited by ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a Russian ship",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_ilmena",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and some dispute having arisen between the sailors and ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Russians",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "killed all the men but two, and carried off most of the women; and about ten years afterwards ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a small schooner",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was sent there from ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to enable the remaining ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", seventeen in number, to quit ",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          13
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The islanders",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "gladly availed themselves of the welcome opportunity, but after all had repaired on board "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "one woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was missing, and she expressed an apprehension that it had been eaten by wild dogs, which infest "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and returned on shore to look for it. In the meantime a gale of wind came up, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was obliged to make sail. Three months after, it again touched at "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to bring away "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but she could not be found; and from that time, although her footprints were occasionally met with on the beach, she herself has not until recently been seen. The remainder of the story will best be told in the language of the narrator:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"At the beginning of the present month an American, "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Niedever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who is now and has long been a resident of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was engaged in otter hunting off "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and touched at "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "While travelling along the beach, to his great astonishment he suddenly came upon ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this woman",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She was engaged in cleaning or curing bird skins, which she sewed together to serve as a covering, and in a garment made of which she was dressed. She did not manifest much surprise at seeing ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Niedever",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "but readily assented to his proposition to leave ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and accompany him to ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his schooner",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She immediately set about making preparations for her departure, and having packed up several bundles of bird skins, and other \"fixings,\" which she had found serviceable in ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she bade adieu for ever to the land where, for so long a time, she might have soliloquized with poetic truth",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"I am monarch of all I survey,\nMy right there is none to dispute;\nFrom the centre all 'round to the sea,\nI am lord of the fowl and the brute.\"",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"I am monarch of all I survey,\nMy right there is none to dispute;\nFrom the centre all 'round to the sea,\nI am lord of the fowl and the brute.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She is now living with "
      },
      {
        "text": "the family of Mr. George Niedever",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "sni",
          "ini",
          "gnijr",
          "jacobni",
          "mrni",
          "mrfni"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she has all her wants administered to. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She is about sixty years old, and is as simple as a child, and quite free from deception and guile.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "One of the reverend clergymen",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", accompanied by the writer, went to see her as soon as he heard of her arrival. He brought with him "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the Mission Indians",
        "entity_key": "natamwoman1",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who could speak the language of one or two tribes of "
      },
      {
        "text": "These Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "carried on a considerable trade with the California Indians. She was greatly delighted to see "
      },
      {
        "text": "this Indian",
        "entity_key": "natamwoman1",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but neither of them could understand a word of what the other said. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She has a distinct articulation for almost every thing she saw, but no one understands her unless when she uses signs and gestures.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She is very contented, and takes great delight in showing to her visitors as well as she can, how she dug the roots, caught the fish, manufactured her garments, and provided generally for her sustenance."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She signifies that she is much better pleased with her present mode of life that she led on ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She takes great delight in looking at horses and cows, having probably never seen such large animals before. On one occasion she caught hold of a horse by the tail, and had it not been that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Niedever",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "called her away, she might probably have suffered severely for her ignorance."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Among the articles she brought along with her from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "were several needles, with which she sewed the birds' skins together. These needles are beautifully made of fish bones, and show a superior degree of ingenuity. The thread which she used was the thin fibres of the sinews of a whale. She has also several fishing hooks made of old nails that she probably found in some boards picked up on the shore. These nails were all bent and sharpened, and attached to a line made of fibres of whale sinews, beautifully twisted together. She had also among her moveables a soft clayey substance like brick, but whether she used this for dressing the birds' skins, or for simply giving a red color to her garments, no one could well make out. Sho had a knife also about an inch long, which seems to have been a piece of iron hoop. It is set in a wooden handle. She brought with her some seal meat, but how she could eat this seems incomprehensible. Ten or twenty yards is about as near as the olfactory nerves would permit any of our party to go to it. She had a quantity of roots which are generally known here by the Indian name of cacometes. In taste they are like the kernel of an unripe nut."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She is a strange speciman of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the race",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and could give expression to her thoughts and feelings, she would be able to add a new chapter to the humanity.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For eighteen years has "
      },
      {
        "text": "this poor creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "lived alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "a desert island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", with no one to share her hopes or her fears, her joys or her sorrows, but the Great Being who gave her life and who has wonderfully preserved it under such extraordinary circumstances."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The learned and pious ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Gonzales",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "regards it as a wonderful instance of the Providence of God, who, in his inscrutable ways has doubtless preserved her up to this time, as were some of her race, in the truths of Christianity.\"",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}